summary.p:
Accordingly, in a first aspect the present invention provides a particle comprising:
(a) a core comprising a benefit agent;
(b) a shell, wherein the shell comprises a polyamide, and wherein the polyamide comprises an aromatic group; and
(c) an optional deposition aid;
wherein the benefit agent comprises 70-100 wt %, by total weight of the benefit agent, of a component selected from tertiary alcohols, alpha substituted aldehydes, aliphatic and aromatic ketones and ketenes and mixtures thereof, excluding cyclic aliphatic materials containing polar functional groups;
and the benefit agent is substantially free from i) aliphatic primary alcohols and ii) aromatic primary alcohols and contains less than 15 wt % of aliphatic aldehydes having a chain length of from 8 to 22, by total weight of the benefit agent.
